    <div class="post-container" id="fpc-2380781">
                      
		<div class="post" id="post-2380781">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,2380781)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-2380781">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser deleted" data-id="1324229"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/common--images/avatars/default/a16.png" alt=""/>(account deleted)</span> <span class="odate time_1443094045 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">24 Sep 2015 11:27</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2380781">
									

<p>Thirding this. It doesn't stand on its own, nor are either of the characters who feature prominently particularly interesting. Also, there are some amazingly wonky lines such as:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>His frizzy hair standing almost straight up, but that's how it normally was and most agents could care less how their hair looks while on duty.</p>
</blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p>He immediately adjusted his slouching posture and tried to suppress any amount of apparent surprise.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">I'm reading all of these out of order, so while this tale was in the <em>middle</em> of &quot;Author Avatar Introduction Month 2015,&quot; rather than the end, it's one of the last Resurrection tales I've read. There's a whiff of it actually setting stuff up for future use, rather than simply saying &quot;here is Junior Comptroller So-and-So! S/he has an unusual defining characteristic!&quot; which is nice. However, after reading 5-6 tales that introduce new, uninteresting characters, I'm pretty well sick of it.</span> Apparently, I already read this tale and downvoted it. The fact that I was unable to remember reading this tale this it is not a good sign.</p>
<p>Reluctant -1</p>

